I was fortunate enough to purchase 5 year CDs with my savings during the past few years. The question for myself is what to do with CDs that continue to come due. Stocks? Gold? Real Estate? My feeling is that stocks will stay about the same, maybe increase slightly, but is the risk worth it? My feeling is No. How about gold? It would not surprise me to see gold fall to $800 or so. Real Estate? In the long run it may be the best investment, but it bothers me that real estate prices are being held artificially high by low interest rates.
